# Default `npm start` (--lan) discovers your Mac from Expo when phone and Mac share Wi-Fi.
#
# If you are on the SAME Wi-Fi but the app still cannot reach the API, common causes:
# - Router "AP / client isolation" or Guest Wi-Fi blocks phone -> laptop (try main SSID or disable isolation).
# - Mac is on Ethernet with a different subnet than the Wi-Fi your phone uses (check both IPs).
# - Expo fell back to 127.0.0.1 on the phone: run `npm run debug:lan-env`, copy EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL into .env here, restart Metro.
#
# Receipt preview calls ScanAndSave on port 8000 on the SAME host as Metro (e.g. 192.168.x.x:8000). Override if needed:
# EXPO_PUBLIC_SCAN_API_URL=http://192.168.1.10:8000
#
# Override kitchen API (copy this file to `.env` in Mobile_ui):
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.1.10:5051
#
# USB + Expo on 127.0.0.1: use `npm run start:localhost`, adb reverse 5051, and keep Backend on the Mac.
